    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for the insight. i've been reading a lot of different stuff though. some people say these hikes are basically a death sentence for local shops because they just can't absorb the cost, while others say it actually helps the local economy by putting more money in people's pockets. from a consultancy perspective, which of those viewpoints is actually more grounded in reality for a small shop like mine?",
